From: Yeoreum Yun <yeoreum.yun@arm.com>
Date: Thu, 3 Jul 2025 19:10:18 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] kasan: remove kasan_find_vm_area() to prevent possible deadlock
Git-commit: 6ee9b3d84775944fb8c8a447961cd01274ac671c
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc6
References: git-fixes CVE-2025-38510 bsc#1248166

find_vm_area() couldn't be called in atomic_context.  If find_vm_area() is
called to reports vm area information, kasan can trigger deadlock like:

CPU0                                CPU1
vmalloc();
 alloc_vmap_area();
  spin_lock(&vn->busy.lock)
                                    spin_lock_bh(&some_lock);
   <interrupt occurs>
   <in softirq>
   spin_lock(&some_lock);
                                    <access invalid address>
                                    kasan_report();
                                     print_report();
                                      print_address_description();
                                       kasan_find_vm_area();
                                        find_vm_area();
                                         spin_lock(&vn->busy.lock) // deadlock!

To prevent possible deadlock while kasan reports, remove kasan_find_vm_area().

Link: https://lkml.kernel.org/r/20250703181018.580833-1-yeoreum.yun@arm.com
Fixes: c056a364e954 ("kasan: print virtual mapping info in reports")
